cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a novel deep-learning-based system for vessel segmentation, which is a common task in computer vision and medical imaging. The proposed method incorporates a graph convolutional network into a unified CNN architecture, which involves both computer vision and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also mentions the use of deep learning and the combination of different types of features, which are related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The experiments involve retinal image datasets and a coronary artery X-ray angiography dataset, which are related to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
